==== SOURCE

http://news.mit.edu/2019/model-predicts-alzheimers-decline-0802

==== AGENT

Oggi Rudovic, MIT MEDIA LAB

==== GOAL

Predict if patients at risk for Alzheimer’s disease will experience significant cognitive decline up to two years in advance.

==== DATA

Biometric data from Alzheimer’s patients and healthy individuals including cognitive test scores collected between biannual doctor’s visits.

==== METHODS

Trained a model to predict how patients will score on cognitive tests between visits. After each doctor visits the model updates score predictions based on newly recorded data.

==== RESULTS

The error rate is not explicitly stated in the article although the results are labelled as “sub-optimal”.

==== COMMENTS

Article is not explicit enough about the effectiveness of the model.

